-- U.S. May Restrict Tax Data Exchange, Widmer-Schlumpf Tells SZ
-- B y   G i l e s   B r o o m
-- 2012-04-29T08:59:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-29/u-s-may-restrict-tax-data-exchange-widmer-schlumpf-tells-sz.html
Switzerland  doesn’t expect the U.S.
to engage in full automatic exchange of information on tax
matters with the Alpine country,  SonntagsZeitung  reported,
citing an interview with Swiss Finance Minister Eveline Widmer- Schlumpf.  Several countries are “firmly interested” in negotiating
withholding tax agreements with Switzerland, the Zurich-based
newspaper also cited the minister as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
